<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Rudo on 06-13-2000 04:30 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I hated this quest. Basically I finally did it by convincing a high-level druid friend to help. He would bind there and when he could time the spawn he would go in and clear it. I also bound there so I could loot the bear. However using this method still took about a month and about 8 bears to finally get the ingot. And what a pain to die and be bound there! The druid kept regular playing hours so I restricted myself to play when he did so I could get a teleport if I died.

Another tip - make friends with the shamen you see down there. I had agreements with four different shamen to tell the other if the bear was spotted. One of them actaully came through for me, although the bear didn't drop the ingot.

The bright side of all this was that me and my druid friend both got a shamen pelt (and burned quite a few). The druid ended up finishing that quest and sold the totemic helm for quite a nice profit. I'm glad he got some reward for helping me (other than free rezzes for life).</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
